properties.name: Calabar-Congo Safe Corridor
properties.description:
Safe overland route from Nigeria to Republic of Congo, bypassing the Anglophone crisis zone in Cameroon and avoiding Equatorial Guinea entirely.

**Total Distance:** 1901 km
**Estimated Drive Time:** 29 hours

## Route Segments:
Calabar → Ikom: ✓ Safe
Ikom → Ekok Border: ⚡ CAUTION
Ekok Border → Mamfe: ⚠️ TRANSIT ONLY
Mamfe → Kumba: ⚠️ TRANSIT ONLY
Kumba → Douala: ✓ Safe
Douala → Edéa: ✓ Safe
Edéa → Yaoundé: ✓ Safe
Yaoundé → Mbalmayo: ✓ Safe
Mbalmayo → Ebolowa: ✓ Safe
Ebolowa → Sangmélima: ✓ Safe
Sangmélima → Djoum: ✓ Safe
Djoum → Mintom: ✓ Safe
Mintom → Kika Border: ⚡ CAUTION
Kika Border → Sembé: ✓ Safe
Sembé → Ouesso: ✓ Safe

## Key Safety Notes:
• **Anglophone Zone (Mamfe-Kumba):** DO NOT stop. Transit in daylight only. Military escorts sometimes available.
• **Douala onwards:** Francophone Cameroon is safe. Normal travel precautions apply.
• **Border crossings:** Have all papers ready. Expect delays but crossings are legitimate.
• **Equatorial Guinea:** Completely avoided - this route stays inland through Yaoundé.

## When to Travel:
• Dry season (Nov-Feb) preferred for road conditions
• Always travel in daylight through Anglophone zone
• Allow 4-5 days for the full crossing with rest stops

properties.name: Calabar
properties.description: Nigerian port city. Entry point. Stock up on supplies, get Cameroon visa stamped. Safe.

properties.name: Ikom
properties.description: Last major Nigerian town before border. Fill fuel tanks. Safe.

properties.name: Ekok Border
properties.description: Nigeria-Cameroon border crossing. Legitimate crossing point. Have papers ready. Modest bribes possible.

properties.name: Mamfe
properties.description: ANGLOPHONE ZONE - DO NOT STOP. Transit only. Military escorts sometimes available from Ekok. Drive in daylight ONLY. No photos.

properties.name: Kumba
properties.description: ANGLOPHONE ZONE - Still dangerous. Continue transit to Douala. Do not stop except for checkpoints.

properties.name: Douala
properties.description: Francophone Cameroon - SAFE. Major port city. Rest stop, resupply, safe hotels. French-speaking zone begins here.

properties.name: Edéa
properties.description: Safe transit town on main highway N3 to Yaoundé.

properties.name: Yaoundé
properties.description: Capital city - SAFE. Major rest stop. Embassies, good hotels, supplies. Can arrange onward travel info here.

properties.name: Mbalmayo
properties.description: Safe town south of Yaoundé. Main route south.

properties.name: Ebolowa
properties.description: Capital of South Region - SAFE. Good stopping point. French-speaking, peaceful area.

properties.name: Sangmélima
properties.description: Safe town. Route continues east toward Congo border.

properties.name: Djoum
properties.description: Small town, limited services but safe. Last significant town before border region.

properties.name: Mintom
properties.description: Remote but safe. Near Congo border.

properties.name: Kika Border
properties.description: Cameroon-Congo border crossing. Small remote post. Have all paperwork ready. May need patience.

properties.name: Sembé
properties.description: First town in Republic of Congo. Safe. Resupply if possible.

properties.name: Ouesso
properties.description: Major town in northern Congo - SAFE. River port on Sangha. Good stopping point. Can continue south to Brazzaville or west to Gabon.
